netrom: Fix use-after-free of a listening socket.

This is an automated ID intended to aid in discovery of potential security vulnerabilities. The actual impact and attack plausibility have not yet been proven.
This ID is fixed in Linux Kernel version v5.10.166 by commit 7de16d75b20ab13b75a7291f449a1b00090edfea, it was introduced in version v5.10.54 by commit 6811744bd0efb9e472cb15d066cdb460beb8cb8a. For more details please see the references link.
